<p>Say, there is an enum - <code>Colors</code> in a file lib.py as,</p>  <pre><code>from flufl.enum import Enum class Colors(Enum):      red = 1      green = 2      blue = 3 </code></pre>  <p>And in my robot file, i am trying to use the Enum, <code>Colors</code> as,</p>  <pre><code>*** Settings *** Library lib.Colors  *** Test Cases *** Print Enum Values         Log To Console  ${red} </code></pre>  <p>It throws error as,</p>  <pre><code>Variable '${red}' not found. </code></pre>  <p>I tried changing import line as <code>Library lib</code> and accessing <code>Colors.red</code>.  Still it fails. </p>  <p>What is the proper way to import and use enum class/variables inside a robot file?</p>